  "body": "<!-- Live body for this quest is a file in the vibers guild. See .claude/skills/quests/SKILL.md. -->\n<!-- Do not edit this row body while the quest is live. -->\n\n## Goal\n\nSimplify the writ status vocabulary from 7–8 muddled values to 6 honest ones, by separating obligation lifecycle from execution state. The key move: demote `waiting` to a query predicate (\"has non-terminal children\"), and — if multi-rig lands — collapse `ready`/`active` into a single `open` since \"is a rig running on this writ\" is a query on the rigs table, not a writ-level fact.",
